H0.text: Complete and incomplete are the two types of digestive systems invertebrates may have.

H1.text: Complete and simple are the two types of digestive systems that invertebrates may have.

H2.text: Complete and fluid are the two types of digestive systems that invertebrates may have.

H3.text: Gastric and monogastric are the two types of digestive systems that invertebrates may have.

A4.text: The human digestive system consists of the gastrointestinal tract plus the accessory organs of digestion.
